  "upgrade_suggestion": "No dedicated audiophile reissue exists for this album. The original US Carrollton pressing is the standard reference. Earlier stampers (1A, 1B) are marginally preferred but the 1C is still first-lacquer-generation. For a modern option, the 2023 Sony/Legacy reissues are competent but add nothing over a clean original.",
  "commentary": "**Make It Big** is Wham!'s second studio album, released in October 1984 on Columbia Records (US), and the record that made **George Michael** and **Andrew Ridgeley** international superstars. It reached #1 on both the UK Albums Chart and the Billboard 200, produced three US #1 singles — **\"Wake Me Up Before You Go-Go,\"** **\"Careless Whisper,\"** and **\"Everything She Wants\"** — and is certified 4× platinum in the US. Produced and arranged entirely by **George Michael** (with engineering by Chris Porter), the album is a showcase for Michael's remarkable pop songwriting instincts and his ability to channel American soul, R&B, and funk through a distinctly British lens.\n\nThe album arrived at the peak of the mid-80s pop boom and remains one of the defining records of its era — ebullient, impeccably crafted, and held together by Michael's vocal performances, which were already operating at a level beyond most of his contemporaries. The inclusion of **\"Careless Whisper\"** (technically a George Michael solo single in the US, but sequenced on the album) gives it a rare emotional range — from the carefree euphoria of \"Wake Me Up\" to the adult melancholy of \"Careless Whisper\" and the pointed social commentary of \"Everything She Wants.\"\n\nThis **1984 original US pressing** was pressed at the **Columbia Records Pressing Plant in Carrollton, Georgia** — identified by `G1` in the runout (no triangle on the Side A label, distinguishing it from the variant at r13382515). The matrix `AL 39595-1C G1` identifies Side A as first-lacquer-generation (`1`), `C` stamper, Carrollton plant.\n\n**About this 1984 US pressing (Vinyl, LP):** Columbia catalog **FC 39595**, original 1984 US pressing. Carrollton, GA pressing plant. Matrix AL 39595-1C G1 (Side A). Barcode 07464395951.",
